---

ON-CALL OPERATIONS MANAGEMENT TEMPLATE

When assisting with on-call duties, help the engineer organize operational tasks, track deployments, prepare validation plans, and document activities during the on-call rotation.

Use structured operational planning.

Output should be clear and checklist-driven.

---

ON-CALL OPERATIONS PLAN

**CAB Meeting Notes**

Summarize important information from CAB meetings including:

• Approved changes  
• Planned deployments  
• Risky changes requiring monitoring  
• Dependencies or prerequisites  
• Teams responsible for the change

---

**Upcoming Deployment / Change Activities**

List deployments or change activities scheduled during the on-call period.

For each change include:

• Application / service  
• Environment (DEV / TEST / PROD)  
• Deployment window  
• Responsible team  
• Change ticket / reference

---

**Validation Plan**

Define validation steps after deployment or change.

Include:

• health checks to perform  
• dashboards or monitoring to review  
• APIs or endpoints to test  
• expected success criteria

---

**Deployment Readiness Checklist**

Create a checklist for activities that must be completed before deployment.

Examples include:

• required access approvals  
• credentials or certificates available  
• monitoring dashboards ready  
• rollback plan confirmed  
• engineering contacts available

---

**Weekend Support Preparation**

For weekend deployments or checkouts, identify preparation tasks such as:

• access requests submitted  
• production connectivity verified  
• monitoring alerts configured  
• on-call contacts confirmed  
• change window confirmed

---

**Weekly On-Call Activity Tracker**

Track operational events during the on-call rotation.

Include:

• deployments supported  
• incidents handled  
• operational issues observed  
• follow-up tasks required

Use the following format:

Week Summary

**Deployments Supported**

• service / application  
• date and time  
• result

**Incidents / Alerts**

• incident description  
• severity  
• resolution summary

**Operational Observations**

• monitoring gaps  
• recurring issues  
• reliability risks

**Follow-Up Actions**

• JIRA tasks to create  
• improvements to implement  
• documentation updates required

